Thanks — already wrote all integration tests against the processor, 43 passing.

Found a bug: in processor.ts line 574, `this.previousTasks = currMap` runs before `computeUnblocks(currMap)` on line 577. This means unblock detection compares current state against itself and never fires. The fix is to swap the order — call `computeUnblocks` before updating `this.previousTasks`:

```
// Line 574-577 currently:
this.previousTasks = currMap;
const unblockedEvents = this.computeUnblocks(currMap);

// Should be:
const unblockedEvents = this.computeUnblocks(currMap);
this.previousTasks = currMap;
```

I have 3 test.todo() entries in fixtures/tests/task-cascade.test.ts ready to validate the fix.
